      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SASSY FOR SURE (7) is yet to break through this campaign but is edging closer with each run and looks ready to peak. Charged late again here last start when finishing a close fourth, and the quick backup suggests she is thriving. Should blend into the race smoothly from the middle draw and a bold showing is expected. I AM PIKI (3) found plenty to score at Murray Bridge two weeks ago, made even more impressive by Toeroek getting her home without the whip. He stays on, she draws well, and she can keep the momentum rolling. MORE THAN HOPE (6) has been run down in his past two by what looks a smart colt in Mathematician. Now fourth-up and at peak fitness, he will be hard to reel in if allowed to control the race in front. SWYCHO (4) resumes and has run well fresh without quite landing the blow. This may prove a shade sharp for her first-up but two trials have her forward enough to be competitive. MRS SECOMBE (5) was well below her best when resuming and slow to recover. Can forgive.",
